# Instinct RPG — Playtest analysis

When Annie provides playtest transcript(s) or asks for post-playtest processing, follow
**`skill-sources/at-playtest-analysis/SKILL.md`** end-to-end.

## Two deliverables (always)

1. **`[date] Playtest Analysis & Design Checklist.md`** — tiered, checkbox, strengths-first
2. **`[date] Discord Recap Post.md`** — story episode recap **before** design takeaways; paste-ready

## Non-negotiables

- **Nathan's debrief statements** = scope authority; separate committed / locked / brainstorm
- **AGENT INFERENCES — VERIFY** section in every checklist
- **Parked ideas** ≠ Tertiary (undecided vs deliberately deferred)
- **Primer teachability** + **on-the-fly rulings** sections required
- Do not edit `design/` from unverified inferences — Annie confirms first (`at-session-close`)

## Agent owns the run

Read full transcripts, write both files, present for verification. No handoffs.

## Open artifacts (required)

After writing the checklist and Discord recap:

1. **Generate browser-readable proof HTML** for each artifact (`.md` does not render on
   GitHub Pages / Simple Browser) — e.g. `jun-30-playtest-analysis-proof.html` and
   `jun-30-discord-recap-proof.html` in the same session folder.
2. **Open both in the Cursor browser** (`browser_navigate`, `position: "active"`) — checklist
   first, Discord recap second (`newTab: true`). Use local `file://` paths immediately; after
   push, also give GitHub Pages URLs for the `*-proof.html` files.
3. Mention both URLs in chat so Annie can re-open them.
